## Subagent Brief: Blocklist Module

Create a new blocklist/ad-blocking module for FastDNS, inspired by grimd.

### ALREADY_KNOWN
- Project: FastDNS, Rust DNS resolver, at `/Users/andrerizzo/Documents/Projects/FastDNS/`
- Config has fields: blocklist_mode, blocklist_sources, blocklist, whitelist, nullroute, nullroute_v6, block_response
- The resolver in `src/resolver/recursive.rs` will call into this module
- Dependencies available: tokio, reqwest, serde, tracing, anyhow, chrono, lru

### TASK
Create `/Users/andrerizzo/Documents/Projects/FastDNS/src/blocklist.rs` module:

```rust
//! Blocklist-based DNS filtering (ad-blocking, malware blocking)
//!
//! Inspired by grimd. Supports:
//! - Automatic download of blocklists from multiple sources
//! - hosts-file and domain-list parsing
//! - In-memory hashset for O(1) domain lookup
//! - Pattern matching for wildcard domains
//! - Whitelist overrides
//! - Periodic refresh of blocklists

use std::collections::{HashMap, HashSet};
use std::sync::Arc;
use std::time::Duration;
use tokio::sync::RwLock;
use tracing::{debug, info, warn};
```

### Required API:

```rust
pub struct Blocklist {
    enabled: bool,
    mode: BlocklistMode,
    blocked: RwLock<HashSet<String>>,
    whitelist: RwLock<HashSet<String>>,
    custom: RwLock<HashMap<String, String>>,
    sources: Vec<String>,
    nullroute_v4: String,
    nullroute_v6: String,
    block_response: BlockResponse,
    stats: RwLock<BlocklistStats>,
}

pub enum BlocklistMode { None, Adblock, Malware, All }
pub enum BlockResponse { Nxdomain, Nullroute }
pub struct BlocklistStats { ... }
```

### Methods:
- `new(config) -> Self` - create from config
- `async fn load(&self)` - download and parse all sources
- `async fn refresh(&self)` - periodic refresh
- `async fn is_blocked(&self, domain: &str) -> Option<BlockAction>` - check domain
- `async fn get_custom(&self, domain: &str) -> Option<String>` - check custom records
- `fn stats(&self) -> BlocklistStats`

### Implementation details:
- Parse hosts files (IP + domain)
- Parse domain lists (one domain per line)
- Strip comments, normalize domains
- Match exact domains and wildcard subdomains
- Whitelist takes priority over blocklist
- Custom DNS records can override everything

Write the complete module to `/Users/andrerizzo/Documents/Projects/FastDNS/src/blocklist.rs`.

Make sure to add `mod blocklist;` - I'll add that to main.rs myself.

### OUTPUT
Return "DONE" when complete.

