content.thinking:
Now I need to fix lines 1360-1364. The issue is:
1. `ns_cache.get(&rec.name).unwrap_or_default()` — With `lru::LruCache::get`, this returns `Option<&Vec<IpAddr>>`. `unwrap_or_default()` on `Option<&Vec<IpAddr>>` doesn't work because `&Vec<IpAddr>: Default` isn't implemented.
2. `ns_cache.insert(rec.name.clone(), new)` → `.put()`

For the `get` + `unwrap_or_default()` issue, I'll use `.cloned().unwrap_or_default()`.

But wait, there's another issue: `let existing = ns_cache.get(&rec.name)...` gives `existing` which is `&Vec<IpAddr>` (or `Vec<IpAddr>` if we use `.cloned()`). Then `if !existing.contains(&ip)` — `Vec::contains` takes `&T`, so if `existing` is `Vec<IpAddr>`, we get `existing.contains(&ip)` which works fine. If `existing` is `&Vec<IpAddr>`, we get `(&Vec<IpAddr>)::contains(&ip)` which also works.

But then `let mut new = existing;` — if `existing` is `&Vec<IpAddr>`, `new` is `&Vec<IpAddr>`. Then `new.push(ip)` won't work because `new` is immutable reference.

If `existing` is `Vec<IpAddr>` (from `.cloned().unwrap_or_default()`), then `new` is `Vec<IpAddr>`, and `new.push(ip)` works. Then `ns_cache.put(rec.name.clone(), new)` works.

So:
```rust
let mut existing = ns_cache.get(&rec.name).cloned().unwrap_or_default();
if !existing.contains(&ip) {
    existing.push(ip);
    ns_cache.put(rec.name.clone(), existing);
}
```

Let me make this change.

